President Trump hosted an Iftar dinner at the White House during Ramadan, expressing gratitude for the presence of ambassadors and dignitaries from countries with large Muslim populations. He highlighted the significance of Ramadan as a time of fasting, prayer, and charity, and emphasized the importance of unity, tolerance, and peace. The President also mentioned recent acts of violence against religious believers and pledged to combat terrorism and religious persecution. He concluded by wishing Muslims around the world Ramadan Kareem and thanking everyone for attending the dinner.